# 9. GOVERNANCE CHANGES ALREADY APPLIED TO MAIN & DEVELOP BRANCHES

As part of the migration and governance implementation activity, the DevOps / Platform Engineering Team has already applied all required repository configuration changes directly to the **main** and **develop** branches of each application repository.

These changes include:

* CI/CD template integration
* Dockerfile standardization
* Gradle configuration updates
* JFrog dependency management integration
* Branch protection policies
* Merge Request approval rules
* Push rules and commit validation policies
* Other migration-related governance controls

### Important for All Developers

The **main** and **develop** branches should now be considered the source of truth for all future development activities.

Before creating any new Feature, Bugfix, Release, or Hotfix branch, please pull the latest changes from the **develop** branch.

Example:

```bash
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop

git checkout -b feature/EPAY-123-new-feature
```

This ensures that all centrally implemented CI/CD, Dockerfile, Gradle, governance, and security configurations are automatically available in your newly created branch.

If you are already working on a branch that was created before the migration activity was completed, you must merge or rebase the latest changes from the **develop** branch before raising a Merge Request.

Failure to do so may result in pipeline failures, merge conflicts, dependency resolution issues, or governance validation errors.

